      "content": "that makes sense. so basically the steel handles the pulling/stretching and the concrete handles the crushing. but if the steel is just sitting inside the concrete, how does it actually work together? like is there any specific reason they work so well as a pair? i heard something about thermal expansion or something like that, but i dont really get how that fits in.",
