      "content": "That's a great follow-up question. The key to the synergy between concrete and steel rebar lies in their different expansion and contraction behavior with temperature changes. When the concrete expands or contracts due to temperature fluctuations, the steel rebar can expand or contract more freely without causing the concrete to crack. This is because steel expands and contracts more linearly than concrete, so the rebar can move more significantly without breaking the bond between the two materials. This allows the concrete to maintain its integrity and resist cracking, even in extreme temperature conditions.",
