      "content": "okay so they expand similar enough that they dont just rip each other apart. but what about the bond itself? if youre just pouring liquid concrete around a bunch of metal bars, how do they actually stay stuck together tightly enough to transfer those loads? is it just friction or is there something else going on with the surface of the rebar?",
